        <td bgcolor="darkslateblue" colspan="2" align="center"><b><font Verdana size="2" color="mintcream">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></b></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td bgcolor='black' valign=top width='100' nowrap><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'><b>Mysk</b></font></td>
        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> This has to do with Amazon.com.</P><P>At the beginning of the month my sweetums purchased me a gift certificate for my BDay.  It was incredibly sweet and selfless of her, in my opinion, considering how very hard she works for her money. This alone made it very very special to me, nevermind the fact that it was for my birthday.</P><P>It was really cool. I had a choice of several merchants to choose from to apply the cert to.  Totally smart idea.</P><P>Well I goofed it by choosing Amazon. :-/  Which will never happen again. . .</P><P>So, I order something from them all happy that she got me something.  This was on Sept. 9th.</P><P>Projected earliest <i>shipping</i> date: September 22nd.</P><P>o_0</P><P>So I wait.. & wait.. and finally decide that if it doesn't ship on the 22nd that I'll get something else. 8:03 PM on the 22nd comes around and still nada.</P><P>I cancel the order and send off an E-Mail to 'em, letting them know that I'm none too happy with how long the shipping was taking. Surprisingly, they respond explaining that it was the type of shipping that I chose and apologized with a $5.00 promotional certificate code.</P><P>Well okay, cool, I can understand that and it sure was nice to toss the $5 into there. . .</P><P>So, this time around I choose 2 - 3 shipping, which tacks on $9.00 and something to the price.</P><P>"Place Order" is clicked -- and web site coughs up an error. >:-/ I chalk it up to Netscape (it was dumb to use it for that) and switch to IE, go through the process of finding the item again, yadda & so forth..</P><P>My $5 cert appears to be eaten.  Wee frustration level grows a little bit more, but I figure it's five bucks that I didn't have in the first place so really, I didn't come out losing much.</P><P>I attempt to place the order, and make up the difference with my credit card.  This is where things get really fun. To skip some detail, I cancelled the order twice.  It appeared that the BDay certificate had been eaten!  No way am I going to put up with THAT.</P><P>After those two cancellations the BDay cert ammount is back.  Okay.  So I try again.  Guess what?  The $5 cert that appeared to be eaten originally pops back up too.  I think, "cool", and click "Place Order" again.</P><P>! Yet again the web site coughs up an error giving a phone number to call.</P><P>Okay! So I do so. I wait on hold for about five to seven minutes before somebody comes on.  No complaints here with the person, they were helpful and polite and put up rather well with my flustered self.</P><P>She has me select the "Payment by check" option, give her the number, and does her ammount-subtracting mojo from her end and the order is <i>finally</i> placed, with all certs applied, from her end.</P><P>Good! Finished that fiasco, right?</P><P>Well, no.</P><P>Projected delivery date: October 10th.<BR>This is September 25th, as of posting this.</P><P>Let's see.. that's... 15 days?</P><P>In closing, I'll remind you that I tacked on $9-something for 2 to 3 day shipping.</P><P>~Mysk<BR>Who will not again ever order from Amazon.com</P><P><a href="http://www.myskyra.net/" target="_blank">http://www.myskyra.net/</a><BR>-<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=294911" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=294911</a></font></td>
      </tr>
